  "ciliary_role": "Mutations in IMPG2 are associated with retinitis pigmentosa and vitelliform macular dystrophy (20673862). When probed with an antibody raised to its C-termi l intracellular domain, IMPG2 immunoreactivity was mostly found within the ellipsoid and myoid zones of the inner segment in normal photoreceptors. In normal photoreceptors, CEP290 allows entry of outer segment-bound proteins while blocking that of inner segment proteins such as STX3, STXBP1, S P25, and IMPG2. In Cep290fl/fl,Cre+ reti s, however, a significant amount of IMPG2 immunoreactivity was detected in outer segments in addition to inner segments (31694913).",
